1
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:09,000
[suspenseful music]

2
00:00:10,750 --> 00:00:12,500
[MAN] According
to eyewitness accounts,

3
00:00:12,708 --> 00:00:15,125
the victims were attacked
by a sudden swarm of eyeballs

4
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:16,458
that flew through the air.

5
00:00:16,458 --> 00:00:19,416
[whimpering]

6
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:33,750
[INK] Aw.

7
00:00:33,958 --> 00:00:35,333
Is she not coming?

8
00:00:35,541 --> 00:00:37,916
[crying]

9
00:00:39,916 --> 00:00:41,458
Flum?

10
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:45,041
Flum?

11
00:00:46,625 --> 00:00:47,916
Flum?

12
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:50,708
Flum?

13
00:00:52,041 --> 00:00:53,291
Flum?

14
00:00:55,625 --> 00:00:57,208
Flum.

15
00:01:02,208 --> 00:01:04,208
Hi, Flum.

16
00:01:06,875 --> 00:01:08,125
What's wrong?

17
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:09,916
Are you OK?

18
00:01:10,125 --> 00:01:11,750
[FLUM] Your face!

19
00:01:11,958 --> 00:01:13,291
Do I have something on it?

20
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:15,625
No. It was earlier.

21
00:01:15,625 --> 00:01:18,041
When I came in, eyeballs were
falling out of your face, Ink.

22
00:01:18,250 --> 00:01:19,166
Huh?

23
00:01:19,375 --> 00:01:20,791
What are you talking about?

24
00:01:20,791 --> 00:01:23,166
You must have been having
some kind of bad dream.

25
00:01:23,375 --> 00:01:24,875
It sounds really scary.

26
00:01:25,083 --> 00:01:27,208
Anyway, where's Milkit?

27
00:01:27,416 --> 00:01:29,625
[FLUM] I wasn't dreaming
or seeing things!

28
00:01:29,625 --> 00:01:31,750
I remember the sounds,
the smells!

29
00:01:31,750 --> 00:01:34,583
You turned into a monster!

30
00:01:34,791 --> 00:01:36,000
That isn't true.

31
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,166
Why would you say
something so mean to me?

32
00:01:38,375 --> 00:01:40,333
Because I know what I saw!

33
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:41,583
You weren't human.

34
00:01:41,791 --> 00:01:42,875
It was awful.

35
00:01:42,875 --> 00:01:44,458
But I am human.

36
00:01:44,458 --> 00:01:46,041
The Church's
tinkering changed you

37
00:01:46,041 --> 00:01:50,125
into something abnormal,
into some sort of creature.

38
00:01:50,333 --> 00:01:52,166
And that's...

39
00:01:52,166 --> 00:01:54,291
why you
don't have a heart.

40
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:56,041
What?

41
00:01:56,041 --> 00:01:57,500
No heart.

42
00:01:57,708 --> 00:02:00,458
That must be why they had
you taking that medicine.

43
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:02,500
It wasn't to keep you healthy
or make you better,

44
00:02:02,708 --> 00:02:04,458
but to suppress your powers.

45
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:08,416
And when you stopped taking it,
things spun out of control.

46
00:02:08,625 --> 00:02:10,000
Those eyeballs,

47
00:02:10,208 --> 00:02:12,041
they hurt people,

48
00:02:12,041 --> 00:02:14,583
and then they even
went after Sarah.

49
00:02:16,166 --> 00:02:17,125
No!

50
00:02:17,333 --> 00:02:18,458
No!

51
00:02:18,666 --> 00:02:20,166
I-- I didn't.

52
00:02:20,375 --> 00:02:21,208
No!

53
00:02:21,416 --> 00:02:22,583
You're wrong.

54
00:02:22,583 --> 00:02:24,708
I wouldn't hurt anyone!

55
00:02:24,916 --> 00:02:28,041
I love Sarah,
and the rest of you!

56
00:02:28,041 --> 00:02:29,833
I love all of you!

57
00:02:30,041 --> 00:02:31,166
Love us?

58
00:02:31,166 --> 00:02:33,125
Ed, Jonny, and Ottilie
are all gone!

59
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:35,875
And now Eterna and Milkit
are missing too!

60
00:02:36,083 --> 00:02:37,416
I can't find them.

61
00:02:37,625 --> 00:02:39,166
[crying]

62
00:02:39,166 --> 00:02:40,500
No!

63
00:02:40,708 --> 00:02:43,166
I never do bad stuff
to people I care about.

64
00:02:43,166 --> 00:02:44,875
You would, and you did!

65
00:02:45,083 --> 00:02:46,750
Don't you see?

66
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:48,500
Friends don't do that!

67
00:02:48,708 --> 00:02:50,291
[suspenseful music]

68
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:52,791
So I guess I'm not a friend.

69
00:02:55,875 --> 00:03:00,125
Then I guess there's
only one place I belong.

70
00:03:02,041 --> 00:03:03,458
[FLUM] Why?

71
00:03:03,666 --> 00:03:05,583
Why is all of this happening?

72
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:09,500
[glass breaking]

73
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:12,583
[DEIN] Flum Apricot!

74
00:03:12,791 --> 00:03:14,458
Get out here.

75
00:03:14,666 --> 00:03:17,750
[theme music]

76
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:54,708
Dein, what are you
doing here?

77
00:04:54,708 --> 00:04:57,500
This poor little guinea pig
ran away from home.

78
00:04:57,708 --> 00:05:00,041
I came to take it
back where it belongs.

79
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:01,416
Hold on.

80
00:05:01,416 --> 00:05:02,875
Did you abduct Milkit?

81
00:05:03,083 --> 00:05:05,166
Mummy girl's
probably being tortured

82
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:07,166
by the lady as we speak.

83
00:05:07,166 --> 00:05:09,916
If she isn't dead already,
that is.

84
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:11,000
The lady?

85
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:13,000
Can't figure it out?

86
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:18,125
I'm talking about the mummy's
former master, Satils Francois.

87
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:19,708
What?

88
00:05:19,916 --> 00:05:21,833
Is that why--

89
00:05:22,041 --> 00:05:23,208
I see.

90
00:05:23,416 --> 00:05:24,708
Hm.

91
00:05:24,708 --> 00:05:26,166
All right.

92
00:05:26,375 --> 00:05:28,708
Come and get me, Flum.

93
00:05:28,708 --> 00:05:30,875
You want to save
your friend, don't you?

94
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:33,458
That's what you call
each other, right?

95
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,875
You're so angry.

96
00:05:41,083 --> 00:05:42,041
I like it, Flum!

97
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:45,208
[melancholic music]

98
00:05:47,875 --> 00:05:48,875
What's wrong?

99
00:05:48,875 --> 00:05:50,458
Don't you want to fight?

100
00:05:50,666 --> 00:05:53,416
[DEIN] Hell of a job keeping
up with me, attagirl.

101
00:05:53,416 --> 00:05:55,333
[FLUM] Ugh! Dein!

102
00:05:55,541 --> 00:05:58,166
I didn't think you'd
follow me so closely.

103
00:05:58,375 --> 00:06:00,416
As much as I'd love
to stay and play,

104
00:06:00,416 --> 00:06:02,041
I've got to get this one home.

105
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:04,458
If you want the girl,
you'll have to fight for her.

106
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:05,875
[FLUM] Come back!

107
00:06:06,083 --> 00:06:09,750
[grunting]

108
00:06:18,291 --> 00:06:20,291
Their teamwork is perfect.

109
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:23,583
It's like they're
moving as one.

110
00:06:23,583 --> 00:06:24,833
How?

111
00:06:25,916 --> 00:06:27,333
Let's see.

112
00:06:27,541 --> 00:06:31,833
Godin Torres, 2,482.

113
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:33,458
A C rank?

114
00:06:33,666 --> 00:06:35,416
Is he the leader, then?

115
00:06:37,708 --> 00:06:39,583
Godin again?

116
00:06:40,916 --> 00:06:45,708
I know this guy,
Grimmie, Dein's lackey.

117
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:48,916
So why's it say Godin?

118
00:06:50,125 --> 00:06:52,125
They all have the same name

119
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:54,833
and the exact same stats.

120
00:06:55,041 --> 00:06:57,083
What's going on?

121
00:07:00,166 --> 00:07:02,583
Something's weird
with their eyes.

122
00:07:02,791 --> 00:07:04,583
The Church must have
messed with them.

123
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:05,708
Here he comes.

124
00:07:05,708 --> 00:07:08,125
[grunting]

125
00:07:09,625 --> 00:07:10,875
Reversal!

126
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:16,291
That's one down.

127
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:19,291
[groaning]

128
00:07:19,291 --> 00:07:22,208
[screaming]

129
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:25,041
[suspenseful music]

130
00:07:26,166 --> 00:07:30,125
Am I supposed to beat
this group by myself?

131
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:33,291
[suspenseful music]

132
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:42,541
No.

133
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:44,375
I will not die.

134
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:49,166
Not here.

135
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:05,000
[GADHIO]
Flum, you know what to do.

136
00:08:05,208 --> 00:08:08,041
Strike the ground
with your prana!

137
00:08:11,125 --> 00:08:13,250
[NARRATOR]
A technique
that overwhelms enemies

138
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:15,458
with a barrage
of sword slashes,

139
00:08:15,666 --> 00:08:18,583
cavalier arts, prana storm.

140
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:26,916
Stay alert.

141
00:08:27,125 --> 00:08:28,000
There are more on the way.

142
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:29,416
Got it.

143
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:32,583
[music playing]

144
00:08:47,041 --> 00:08:50,000
[heavy breathing]

145
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:58,125
Thanks, Gadhio.

146
00:08:59,458 --> 00:09:01,125
You came to help.

147
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,041
Yeah.

148
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:05,833
Some girl named Sarah
asked me to.

149
00:09:09,416 --> 00:09:11,708
Does that mean

150
00:09:11,916 --> 00:09:14,125
she's alive?

151
00:09:14,125 --> 00:09:15,916
Yes.

152
00:09:16,125 --> 00:09:18,125
[NARRATOR]
Flum had been
shrouded in despair,

153
00:09:18,125 --> 00:09:21,291
certain that she'd lost
everyone she held dear.

154
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:22,833
But with those words,

155
00:09:23,041 --> 00:09:25,708
a ray of hope
broke through the darkness.

156
00:09:27,458 --> 00:09:29,291
Right, then.

157
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,666
Let's move.

158
00:09:42,125 --> 00:09:43,416
Link up.

159
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:45,000
Connection.

160
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,250
[GADHIO] Flum!

161
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:53,250
Leave me.

162
00:09:54,708 --> 00:09:55,666
Run.

163
00:09:55,875 --> 00:09:57,291
I'll handle this fight.

164
00:09:57,500 --> 00:10:00,291
[suspenseful music]

165
00:10:03,208 --> 00:10:05,208
My, my.

166
00:10:05,416 --> 00:10:07,000
You're quite the beast.

167
00:10:07,208 --> 00:10:08,250
[GADHIO] One of the children?

168
00:10:08,250 --> 00:10:10,833
Ink must have
blabbed about us.

169
00:10:11,041 --> 00:10:12,208
That useless idiot.

170
00:10:12,416 --> 00:10:13,625
Oh, well.

171
00:10:15,208 --> 00:10:17,875
Now, spiral monster,

172
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:20,500
you will die.

173
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:22,375
It's your funeral, mister.

174
00:10:22,583 --> 00:10:24,541
Connection.

175
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:27,375
Just hold on a little longer,

176
00:10:27,583 --> 00:10:30,541
Milkit, Ink.

177
00:10:34,083 --> 00:10:35,500
Interesting.

178
00:10:35,708 --> 00:10:37,750
There's a hidden passageway.

179
00:10:37,958 --> 00:10:41,208
You can get inside by going
through the stable in the yard.

180
00:10:43,458 --> 00:10:45,041
A Church lapdog.

181
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:01,458
[DEIN] I thought you'd
never show, Miss Apricot.

182
00:11:01,666 --> 00:11:05,833
I welcome you to the mansion
of Satils Francois.

183
00:11:05,833 --> 00:11:07,875
Take me to Ink and Milkit.

184
00:11:08,083 --> 00:11:09,541
Don't know where they are.

185
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:12,083
You should worry more about
keeping yourself alive.

186
00:11:12,291 --> 00:11:13,291
Ha.

187
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:16,041
You're the one
who's gonna die!

188
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,333
Hyah!

189
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:22,250
Prepare for an early grave,
Dein.

190
00:11:40,625 --> 00:11:42,791
[DEIN] Your powers
are so annoying.

191
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:46,375
Yeah. Right back at you, Dein.

192
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:47,916
Did you get
those gross abilities

193
00:11:48,125 --> 00:11:50,250
for joining
the Church of Origin?

194
00:11:50,458 --> 00:11:51,500
Yeah, sure did.

195
00:11:51,708 --> 00:11:53,041
Like 'em?

196
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:58,083
So that's the reason
you sold out your friends!

197
00:11:58,291 --> 00:12:00,125
You'd do the exact
same thing.

198
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:02,583
Imagine to be offered
absolute power

199
00:12:02,791 --> 00:12:05,541
that money and influence
could never match!

200
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:08,125
A power that could
change the very laws

201
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:09,250
that govern this world!

202
00:12:09,458 --> 00:12:10,291
Huh?

203
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,541
[DEIN] Admit it.

204
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:15,250
You'd make the same choice.

205
00:12:15,458 --> 00:12:18,708
[suspenseful music]

206
00:12:29,416 --> 00:12:31,458
[cackling]

207
00:12:31,666 --> 00:12:34,250
So how do you like
the Francois mansion?

208
00:12:34,458 --> 00:12:38,125
Mummy girl's former master
has some nasty proclivities,

209
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:40,333
wouldn't you say?

210
00:12:40,541 --> 00:12:43,500
Those tentacles bat away
any regular attacks,

211
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:45,916
which means...

212
00:12:49,541 --> 00:12:52,291
Prana shaker.

213
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,416
[laughter]

214
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:56,916
Not your lucky day.

215
00:12:59,916 --> 00:13:02,041
You're too slow.

216
00:13:05,666 --> 00:13:07,000
Come on!

217
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:09,666
You usually have more guts
when you face me!

218
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,333
Nowhere to run.

219
00:13:14,541 --> 00:13:18,375
About time I got
my hands on you.

220
00:13:18,583 --> 00:13:20,125
My friends are dead.

221
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:22,833
My humanity is gone.

222
00:13:23,041 --> 00:13:25,208
A situation like that
really makes you think

223
00:13:25,416 --> 00:13:27,458
about what you've got left.

224
00:13:27,666 --> 00:13:29,583
But today
I finally get to cross

225
00:13:29,791 --> 00:13:32,250
one big regret off of my list!

226
00:13:32,458 --> 00:13:34,041
Your life is mine, Flum.

227
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:37,041
Sure, the lady told me
not to kill you.

228
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:39,333
I just don't care
about her orders.

229
00:13:39,541 --> 00:13:42,083
And I don't think
I can hold myself back.

230
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:45,708
Your death is the start
of my comeback.

231
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:49,125
I'll rule
the West District again.

232
00:13:49,333 --> 00:13:51,791
Actually,
with my new strength,

233
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,666
I'll take over the entire
kingdom this time.

234
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:56,916
I'll rule everything!

235
00:13:57,125 --> 00:13:59,083
[WOMAN]
Create a picture in your mind

236
00:13:59,291 --> 00:14:02,125
and say the words
that come naturally.

237
00:14:02,958 --> 00:14:05,000
Re-- Reaper.

238
00:14:05,875 --> 00:14:07,625
Your time's run out.

239
00:14:07,833 --> 00:14:09,125
Goodbye.

240
00:14:10,291 --> 00:14:13,583
[STRAINING] Reaper Soul.

241
00:14:23,791 --> 00:14:25,041
What did you do?

242
00:14:25,250 --> 00:14:26,333
Damn it!

243
00:14:28,791 --> 00:14:30,333
Ah!

244
00:14:30,541 --> 00:14:33,291
The tentacles are rotting away.

245
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:35,000
[NARRATOR]
Flum had only to picture them

246
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:37,583
loosening their grip on her.

247
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,833
Reversal!

248
00:14:44,291 --> 00:14:45,291
No.

249
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:46,500
This can't be happening.

250
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:49,125
You cannot defeat the divine!

251
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:52,458
Isn't this the Great Origin's
power that I'm wielding?

252
00:14:55,041 --> 00:14:56,416
Pathetic.

253
00:14:56,625 --> 00:14:57,666
That's what you deserve

254
00:14:57,666 --> 00:14:59,750
for relying on the gifts
of others.

255
00:14:59,958 --> 00:15:02,541
You're still nothing!

256
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:04,333
I won't let you beat me!

257
00:15:04,541 --> 00:15:08,416
[FLUM] Prana shaker, reversal.

258
00:15:15,166 --> 00:15:16,791
Amazing.

259
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,791
Even Origin's power
can be reversed.

260
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:22,500
[gasping]

261
00:15:23,583 --> 00:15:26,583
[VOICES]
It's a voice
of corruption.

262
00:15:26,791 --> 00:15:29,333
Flum Apricot,
you mustn't listen

263
00:15:29,541 --> 00:15:31,583
to the voice of corruption.

264
00:15:31,791 --> 00:15:34,125
It's a voice of corruption.

265
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:36,916
Flum Apricot, you musn't--

266
00:15:37,125 --> 00:15:38,208
Damn.

267
00:15:38,416 --> 00:15:40,333
Those voices again,

268
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:42,750
the lady and Origin.

269
00:15:44,416 --> 00:15:47,458
Why are they so scared
of the slave girl?

270
00:15:47,666 --> 00:15:49,750
Stop mumbling your excuses.

271
00:15:49,958 --> 00:15:51,291
You're weak.

272
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:53,833
Do you really think
you've beaten me?

273
00:15:54,041 --> 00:15:56,125
The battle's just
getting started.

274
00:15:56,916 --> 00:15:59,875
I've barely begun to fight.

275
00:16:00,083 --> 00:16:03,291
Behold the power
Origin granted me,

276
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:06,625
fueled by the dark crystal
embedded within my body!

277
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:08,041
What?

278
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:12,041
Ink shows no signs
of having a heartbeat.

279
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:15,625
But there's something
that's keeping her alive.

280
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:18,708
Does Ink have a dark
crystal in her body too?

281
00:16:19,541 --> 00:16:21,208
The power
of the core gives me

282
00:16:21,416 --> 00:16:25,125
the strength to slaughter
any fool that stands in my way!

283
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:26,375
[FLUM] The core?

284
00:16:27,458 --> 00:16:29,333
[WOMAN] You broke its core?

285
00:16:35,041 --> 00:16:36,666
[laughter]

286
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:38,000
Take her body.

287
00:16:38,208 --> 00:16:39,458
Make it painful.

288
00:16:39,458 --> 00:16:42,250
Become a mindless ball
of meat, you bitch!

289
00:16:42,458 --> 00:16:44,750
Scream for me and die!

290
00:16:44,958 --> 00:16:46,875
[screaming]

291
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:51,458
You think that'll help?

292
00:16:52,875 --> 00:16:56,791
Ink didn't know eyeballs
were falling out of her face

293
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,916
or attacking people.

294
00:16:59,958 --> 00:17:02,625
So this power--

295
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:04,625
Hey. What gives?

296
00:17:04,833 --> 00:17:06,041
Why did you stop?

297
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:08,166
Defend me like you always do!

298
00:17:08,375 --> 00:17:09,458
Take Flum!

299
00:17:09,666 --> 00:17:11,416
Save it.

300
00:17:11,625 --> 00:17:14,083
These eyes, they belong to Ink.

301
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:16,125
She's the one
that's in charge here.

302
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:18,208
This is how
she protects her friends.

303
00:17:18,416 --> 00:17:19,208
Ha!

304
00:17:19,416 --> 00:17:21,708
This power is mine.

305
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:23,291
Origin told me so.

306
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:25,041
They tricked you.

307
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:28,166
It made you easy to control.

308
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:31,375
You seem desperate.

309
00:17:31,583 --> 00:17:34,166
I'm with the Church, child.

310
00:17:34,375 --> 00:17:37,000
And I'm willing
to lend you a hand.

311
00:17:37,208 --> 00:17:39,583
[NARRATOR]
In that moment,
Dein understood

312
00:17:39,791 --> 00:17:40,750
that he had been fooled

313
00:17:40,958 --> 00:17:42,166
and that he would fall

314
00:17:42,375 --> 00:17:44,750
for the same ruse again
even now.

315
00:17:44,958 --> 00:17:49,333
[VOICES] [murmuring]

316
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:50,666
[DEIN] It can't be!

317
00:17:50,875 --> 00:17:53,333
This power belongs
to me, not her.

318
00:17:53,541 --> 00:17:55,333
Defend me, damn it!

319
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:58,208
I said such awful things
to Ink.

320
00:17:58,416 --> 00:18:03,000
And yet, despite that,
she's protecting me.

321
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:07,833
I have to apologize to her.

322
00:18:08,041 --> 00:18:10,208
Now, where is Ink, damn it?

323
00:18:13,083 --> 00:18:15,875
[melancholic music]

324
00:18:16,083 --> 00:18:17,416
[DEIN] It makes no sense.

325
00:18:17,625 --> 00:18:20,500
How could someone like
me lose to a slave?

326
00:18:20,708 --> 00:18:22,000
I was a ruler.

327
00:18:22,208 --> 00:18:24,125
We lost our nobility.

328
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:26,958
I had to struggle
in those damn slums.

329
00:18:27,166 --> 00:18:29,791
I clawed my way up
with my own two hands.

330
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,208
I-- I am a champion
of the people.

331
00:18:33,416 --> 00:18:36,041
I spent years
building an empire.

332
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:39,125
Then, out of nowhere,
these monsters show up

333
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:41,500
and destroy
all that I've built!

334
00:18:41,708 --> 00:18:43,208
It's no fair.

335
00:18:43,416 --> 00:18:46,416
It's not how my story
is supposed to play out.

336
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:48,000
Screw the Church.

337
00:18:48,208 --> 00:18:49,708
Screw the children.

338
00:18:49,916 --> 00:18:51,166
Screw Origin.

339
00:18:51,375 --> 00:18:53,000
Fuck 'em all,

340
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:55,916
and fuck you!

341
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,625
What the hell?

342
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,333
No way.

343
00:19:02,541 --> 00:19:04,833
How could you beat me?

344
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:07,208
You're pathetic.

345
00:19:07,416 --> 00:19:09,750
The people I used to know
are all dead,

346
00:19:09,958 --> 00:19:12,458
every last friend of mine.

347
00:19:12,666 --> 00:19:15,458
So what am I
supposed to do now?

348
00:19:15,666 --> 00:19:17,625
You're the one
who betrayed them.

349
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:19,125
They believed in you.

350
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:20,750
They followed you.

351
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:23,708
But you took their wills
away and made them pawns.

352
00:19:25,083 --> 00:19:28,375
You have no right to complain
after what you did!

353
00:19:28,583 --> 00:19:30,666
[DEIN] Why are you
getting mad at me?

354
00:19:30,875 --> 00:19:32,500
Wait.

355
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:35,125
You're pretending that you're
a noble hero again, aren't you?

356
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:38,000
I allowed my old friends
to make themselves useful.

357
00:19:38,208 --> 00:19:39,291
They should thank me.

358
00:19:39,291 --> 00:19:42,083
Yeah.
Keep telling yourself that.

359
00:19:42,291 --> 00:19:44,708
Try to pretend you
didn't abandon them.

360
00:19:44,916 --> 00:19:46,541
I had no choice.

361
00:19:46,750 --> 00:19:48,958
I didn't plan it
this way either.

362
00:19:49,166 --> 00:19:50,583
Blame Carnis.

363
00:19:50,583 --> 00:19:54,041
That oaf is the one who
turned on his own partner.

364
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:55,666
Don't look at me like that.

365
00:19:55,875 --> 00:19:57,666
Imagine you had to choose
between your life

366
00:19:57,875 --> 00:19:59,166
and your friendships.

367
00:19:59,166 --> 00:20:01,250
If you were forced
to pick one or the other,

368
00:20:01,458 --> 00:20:04,458
I'm sure you'd make the same
decision that I did!

369
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:06,250
[FLUM] I'm not like you.

370
00:20:06,458 --> 00:20:08,083
There's no way
I'd ever sacrifice

371
00:20:08,291 --> 00:20:10,625
the people I hold dear to me.

372
00:20:10,833 --> 00:20:13,916
How can you cling
to such idealistic nonsense?

373
00:20:14,125 --> 00:20:17,458
Did you forget your friend
sold you into slavery?

374
00:20:17,666 --> 00:20:20,916
You're this close to ending up
exactly like me!

375
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:23,208
[melancholic music]

376
00:20:23,416 --> 00:20:26,750
[FLUM] You're seriously trying
to get me to take pity on you?

377
00:20:28,166 --> 00:20:29,375
To coddle you?

378
00:20:29,583 --> 00:20:30,708
Disgusting.

379
00:20:32,291 --> 00:20:33,833
Disgusting?

380
00:20:34,041 --> 00:20:35,208
Forgive me.

381
00:20:35,916 --> 00:20:37,500
[NARRATOR]
Dein had lost everything--

382
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:40,916
his power, his fame,
his friends,

383
00:20:41,125 --> 00:20:42,416
his place in the world.

384
00:20:42,625 --> 00:20:44,333
All he had left
was a fragile ego

385
00:20:44,541 --> 00:20:46,208
and his obsession with Flum.

386
00:20:46,416 --> 00:20:50,791
And now, even that ego
was in tatters.

387
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,958
No, no.

388
00:20:53,166 --> 00:20:56,416
What drove me, what
made me do this was--

389
00:20:56,625 --> 00:20:58,458
[VOICES]
You want to do this.

390
00:20:58,666 --> 00:20:59,541
No.

391
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:02,291
Please, stay out of my head!

392
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:04,208
Stop-- get it under control.

393
00:21:04,416 --> 00:21:05,833
[VOICES]
You want to do this.

394
00:21:06,041 --> 00:21:07,000
What's the next?

395
00:21:07,208 --> 00:21:09,083
You want want to be this.

396
00:21:09,291 --> 00:21:11,166
[FLUM] What's going on?

397
00:21:11,375 --> 00:21:13,541
I will kill you.

398
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:16,125
[melancholic music]

399
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:17,708
Flum,

400
00:21:17,916 --> 00:21:22,583
if only you hadn't shown up,

401
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:24,666
my dream would--

402
00:21:26,083 --> 00:21:28,875
Dein said he had
a core inside of him.

403
00:21:30,458 --> 00:21:33,833
If that's so, he can die.

404
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:35,750
I will end this!

405
00:21:37,625 --> 00:21:40,458
Reversal!

406
00:21:40,666 --> 00:21:43,750
[melancholic music]

407
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:50,500
[shrieking]

408
00:21:58,166 --> 00:21:59,958
So much misery.

409
00:22:00,166 --> 00:22:03,208
How many people did you
sacrifice for your dream?

410
00:22:04,708 --> 00:22:07,166
Wallow in regret as you die.

411
00:22:08,875 --> 00:22:12,125
[theme music]
